dialogue concerning the two chief world.data-term: dialogue concerning the two chief world systems

examples.en: Galileo professed that in the moon there is no rain.
Galileo wrote in the vernacular to reach a larger audience.
The commissioners entered into an active correspondence with Galileo.
Galileo proposed the heliocentric theory that the Earth goes around the sun.
Using a telescope, Galileo discovered stars that were invisible to the naked eye.
Galileo was condemned as a heretic for supporting Copernicus's thesis that the earth revolves around the sun and not vice versa.
